        <div class="text-5xl text-center py-5 dark:text-gray-300">
          About
        </div>
        <div class="markdown dark:text-gray-300">
          <p>Hello! I&rsquo;m a freelance data scientist with an interest in web development. When I&rsquo;m not freelancing, I build data driven web-apps like <a href="https://pippip.email">PipPip.email</a> and <a href="https://moneybar.nl">MoneyBar.nl</a>. </p>
<p>As a data-scientist I specialise in finance and blockchain domains. I&rsquo;m an expert python developer, and there&rsquo;s a tonne of things I still want to learn about web development and data science. I enjoy working with <code>Django</code>, <code>Wagtail</code>, <code>TensorFlow</code>, and <code>Plotly</code> in particular. I designed this blog using <code>pelican</code> and <code>tailwind</code> <span class="caps">CSS</span>.</p>
<p>Here is a brief history of my career so far, there&rsquo;s more information on my <a href="https://johnmathews.eu/experience">experience</a>&nbsp;page:</p>
<p>In 2020 I succeeded in building awesome web apps, and failed horribly at
marketing&nbsp;them.</p>
<p>In 2019 I began freelancing as a data specialist at Uber and as a senior Data
Scientist at&nbsp;Shell</p>
<p>In 2018 I joined a Blockport, a startup Cryptocurrency exchange, as their only Data Specialist. I built the tools we needed to answer questions and collect&nbsp;metrics.</p>
<p>In 2017 I qualified as a chartered accountant and became a financial&nbsp;consultant.</p>
<p>In 2014 I moved to London and began work as an external financial auditor for banking clients. I also began qualifying as a chartered accountant with the <a href="https://careers.icaew.com/en/why-a-career-in-chartered-accountancy/why-become-an-icaew-chartered-accountant"><span class="caps">ICAEW</span></a>.</p>
<p>In 2010 I began my PhD researching granular materials at the <a href="https://www.baunat.boku.ac.at/igt/">University of Natural Resources and Life Sciences</a> in Vienna,&nbsp;Austria.</p>
<p>In 2009 I graduated from Edinburgh University with a masters degree in Civil Engineering. The  <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Great_Recession">Great Recession</a> had arrived and I found a job at Starbucks. This made me curious about finance and I resolved to one day understand <a href="https://www.lrb.co.uk/v40/n13/john-lanchester/after-the-fall">how banks work</a>.</p>
<p>You can find me on <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/johnmathews1">LinkedIn</a> and on <a href="http://www.github.com/johnmathews">GitHub</a>.</p>
<p>Information about my work researching silos and granular flows can be found <a href="https://johnmathews.eu/silos">here</a>. If you&rsquo;d like to know when I publish something new on this site, please subscribe for updates. I don&rsquo;t send emails as often as I make new&nbsp;posts.</p>
<p>I think that <a href="https://blog.samaltman.com/the-days-are-long-but-the-decades-are-short">this</a> is generally good advice, and <a href="https://www.fs.blog/mental-models/">this</a> is a useful set of tools.
â€” <a href="http://twitter.com/johnmathews">@johnmathews</a></p>
